content.description: Sit start on jug on lower right side of the face (red). Feet follow hands. Two foot nubs along right side of crack are on (marked w blue dots), chalky pinch on right side of crack is on (marked w blue arrow). Top out with two hands to the lip left of the last hold (green)

Start as for the classic 4-rock problem, matched with texture feet, bump left and slam dunk the pockety crimp above. Move up through tension-y sequence to a somewhat desperate move to the finishing block. Texture/nubbins only for feet
Sit start on big jug (red). Make big throws up the wall, finishing on the big horn (green). Wall texture only (pebbles, smears) for feet (ie no putting feet on earlier handholds)

Rules:

Important

: Keep your left limbs on the left side of the crack and your right limbs on the right side of the crack. No crossovers.

All Rocks Feet (ARF) - Use any footholds necessary

All holds on

Crack is off
Start on marginal holds (red) with good foot. Move up to roof on crimps and follow juggy crack to top out over the top. Feet follow hands (circled holds only)

Please check out

https://bumbu.me/husky-rock/

.... Not my site, but its super helpful for seeing routes.

Rainbow coalition is a no rocks feet (i.e. can only smear on the texture of the wall). Start on the left side and finish on the last hold to the right. Felt hard at first, but got easier after finding better beta. I personally did a rose move for the second to last hold and that sequence felt about v4. Feel free to give your opinions so we can get more consensus!
content.protection: none, short wall so the pebbles are fine
content.location: Inner side of the overhung wall

content.description:
Start matched on 'Texas' hold and work up to a crumbly pocket in the crack under the roof. Set up on the two crimps and make a fun toss up to the top. Shorter climbers have a few foot and bump options to reach the key sloper at about 7' height, but these may make the route harder and more technical for the grade

Started working on this to train for some movement on Chain Reaction (12c) at Smith. Turned out to be A LOT easier than the beast herself when I finally got down there.
Start on opposing sidepulls (red). Feet follow hands (blue). Top out over the top (green)
content.location: Feel free to add FA or other name

content.description: Start two hands on sloper (red), moving up right-facing sidepulls to finish (green). Feet follow hands (blue circled holds only)

Showed this project I was working on to a husky rock veteran and was told it follows a similar line to a classic problem called 'Firewalker' (V9?) but with an easier start and a shorter, less X-rated topout. Worth adding in my book as a more accessible variation.

Texture/nubbins only for feet. Can be climbed using the slab on the left for feet (smears only) for V3-4, or with the slab off for V4-5. Start matched on jug and move up to pinch the left side of the crack (left side only, no jamming, look for secret thumb beta). Continue to finishing block
content.protection: Look out for the slab on the left as you move up this route. The slab is the namesake 'Fire' for the original route and this variation

content.description:
Please check out

bumbu.me/husky-rock/

.... Not my site, but its super helpful for seeing routes. Just wanted to give credit to this dev for the work he did to put all of these up.

I started matched and threw my feet onto a rock below. Rocks can be used as feet for this one, but there's also a slightly harder sit start version that's "no rocks feet". One move wonder, but it's super fun. Kind of feels like Skidmarks at Fridge.

Harder version didn't make it much harder tbh.
content.protection: none, short wall so pebbles on ground are fine
content.location: Wall perpendicular to slab that faces north.

content.description: Start sitting and bump right, then move up through a powerful match to pinch the crack (left side is on only, no jamming) and toss to the finishing block. Texture/nubbins only for feet, no rock holds. Starting movement reminded the FA of pitching out of a windup
content.protection: Watch out for the corner of the tower behind you, particularly on the finishing move. I never hit it or felt like I was going to in many sessions of working this, but it might be worth having someone spot you, especially if this is close to your limit

content.description: Start on left side of the south tower. Move right and then up through technical and delicate moves, using blue circled holds for hands and any holds or texture for feet. Crux foot moves will likely require a mixture of rock holds and texture nubbins to navigate up to the juggy sidepull. Cracks are off. Top out onto ledge to the right

Please check out

bumbu.me/husky-rock/

.... Not my site, but its super helpful for seeing routes and wanted to give credit to this dev for his hard work!

No rocks feet (i.e. rocks can't be used for feet, just texture of wall).

Start matched down low and then hit a crimp etched into the texture of the wall. Pounce up to the jug. Find some good feet to make a throw to the last hold before topping out.
content.protection: none, not very tall wall so pebbles in ground are fine
content.location: East side of the south facing wall.
